The paper deals with the problem of spatio-temporal range search, which involves indexing and searching data based on both spatial and temporal information. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including databases (cs.DB), data structures (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
